{"lemma":"نِسْبَةٌ","slug":"نِسْبَةٌ","root":"ن.س.ب","root_slug":"ن-س-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-س-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adv","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39700"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of نَسَبَ (nasaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"relationship, affiliation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"connection, relation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"agreement"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ratio, proportion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rate","examples":[{"text":"اِنْخَفَضَتْ نِسْبَةُ ٱلْبِطَالَةِ فِي ٱلسَّنَوَاتِ ٱلْأَخِيرَةِ.","english":"The unemployment rate has decreased in recent years."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"percentage","examples":[{"text":"تَدْرُسُ نِسْبَةٌ كَبِيرَةٌ مِنَ ٱلشَّبَابِ فِي ٱلْخَارِجِ.","english":"A big percentage of young people study abroad."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nisba, a common suffix to form adjectives of relation or pertinence, e.g. ـي (-ī, -iyy) m and ـيَة (-íyya) f."},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in proportion to, in comparison with"},{"pos":"adv","gloss":"in allusion to, after (as in \"named after\")","examples":[{"text":"جَامِعُ الفَاتِحُ سُمَّى نِسْبَةً لِلسُّلْطَانِ مُحَمَّدِ الفَاتِحِ","english":"Fatih Mosque was named after the sultan Mehmed the Conqueror."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of نَسَبَ (nasaba).\n\nAdverbial accusative of نِسْبَة (nisba, “relationship”)."},"ipa":["/nis.ba/","/nis.ba.tan/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39700","headword_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ","root":"nsb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Relation; proportion; comparison;"},{"kind":"text","text":"with respect to quantity, or measure, and the like. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasabN","text_ar":"نَسَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"binisobapi ka*aA","text_ar":"بِنِسْبَةِ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In proportion to such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapu AlEa$arapi A_ilaY AlmiAy^api","text_ar":"نِسْبَةُ العَشَرَةِ اـِلَى المِايَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The proportion of ten to a hundred is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of a tenth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-  [You also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAln~isobapi A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"بِالنِّسْبَةِ اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In relation to,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in comparison with, such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A name of relation to a father, mother, tribe, town"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"district, art"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trade, &c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalawiY~N","text_ar":"عَلَوِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faATimiY~N","text_ar":"فَاطِمِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qura$iY~N","text_ar":"قُرَشِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mak~iY~N","text_ar":"مَكِّىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawohariY~N","text_ar":"جَوْهَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] ending with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y~","text_ar":"ىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". A more general name of this kind should precede a more particular one: thus you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqura$iY~u AlhaA$imiY~u","text_ar":"القُرَشِىُّ الهَاشِمِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and it is better that a name of relation to a tribe should precede one of relation to a town or the like: thus you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqura$iY~u Almak~iY~u","text_ar":"القُرَشِىُّ المَكِّىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". It is said that the Arabs originally called themselves by such names only in relation to tribes; and that, when they took up their abodes in cultivated lands and in cities, they borrowed names of relation to towns and the like from the Persians and Copts. (Msb.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munaAsabapN","text_ar":"مُنَاسَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tanaAsubN","text_ar":"تَنَاسُبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Resemblance; similarity; conformity; analogy; correspondence; suitableness; fitness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Al$~ayoy^ayoni nsbpN","text_ar":"بَيْنَ الشَّيْيَيْنِ نسبةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mnAsbpN","text_ar":"مناسبةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tnAsbN","text_ar":"تناسبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between the two things is a resemblance, &c."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA nsbpN qariybapN","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا نسبةٌ قَرِيبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them two is a near resemblance, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisobapN Hukomiy~apN","text_ar":"نِسْبَةٌ حُكْمِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"relation of a predicate to its subject"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in books on logic).]"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}